  },
  "tool_calls": [
    {
      "name": "Bash",
      "args": {
        "command": "ls; cat stm32-project.jsonc 2>/dev/null || find . -maxdepth 2 -name \"stm32-project.jsonc\" -exec cat {} \\;",
        "description": "Locate and show project descriptor"
      }
    },
    {
      "name": "Grep",
      "args": {
        "pattern": "USART2|AF7|GPIO_AF7",
        "path": "Projects/NUCLEO-L476RG/Examples",
        "output_mode": "content",
        "-n": true,
        "head_limit": 40
      }
    },
    {
      "name": "Bash",
      "args": {
        "command": "sed -n 60,135p Projects/NUCLEO-L476RG/Examples/PWR/VCP-ECHO/Src/main.c",
        "description": "Show VCP-ECHO GPIO/USART2 config code"
      }
    },
    {
      "name": "Bash",
      "args": {
        "command": "stm32 debug read-peripheral GPIO GPIOA Projects/NUCLEO-L476RG/Examples/PWR/VCP-ECHO/STM32CubeIDE/Debug/VCP-ECHO.elf 2>&1 | tail -60",
        "description": "Read live GPIOA registers via SVD-decoded debug recipe"
      }
    },
    {
      "name": "Bash",
      "args": {
        "command": "stm32 prog list-probes 2>&1 | tail -30",
        "description": "List attached ST-LINK probes"
      }
    },
    {
      "name": "Bash",
      "args": {
        "command": "sed -n 135,190p Projects/NUCLEO-L476RG/Examples/PWR/VCP-ECHO/Src/main.c",
        "description": "Show USART2_Config GPIO alternate-function setup"
      }
    },
    {
      "name": "Bash",
      "args": {
        "command": "STM32_PROGRAMMER_DEFAULT_SN=066DFF485754727567021514 stm32 debug read-peripheral GPIO GPIOA Projects/NUCLEO-L476RG/Examples/PWR/VCP-ECHO/STM32CubeIDE/Debug/VCP-ECHO.elf 2>&1 | python3 -c \"import json,sys; d=json.load(sys.stdin); regs=d.get('registers',d); print(json.dumps({k:v for k,v in (regs.items() if isinstance(regs,dict) else [])} if not isinstance(regs,list) else regs, indent=1)[:3000])\"",
        "description": "Read live GPIOA via L476RG probe, show registers"
      }
    },
    {
      "name": "Bash",
      "args": {
        "command": "STM32_PROGRAMMER_DEFAULT_SN=066DFF485754727567021514 stm32 debug read-peripheral GPIOA Projects/NUCLEO-L476RG/Examples/PWR/VCP-ECHO/STM32CubeIDE/Debug/VCP-ECHO.elf 2>&1 | python3 -c \"\nimport json,sys\nd=json.load(sys.stdin)\nregs=d.get('registers') or []\nfor r in regs:\n    n=r.get('name','')\n    if n in ('MODER','AFRL','AFRH','OTYPER','PUPDR'):\n        print(n, r.get('value'))\n        for f in r.get('fields',[]):\n            if any(p in f.get('name','') for p in ('2','3')) and not f['name'].endswith(('12','13')):\n                print('  ', f['name'], '=', f.get('value'))\n\" ",
        "description": "Read live GPIOA, extract MODER/AFRL fields for PA2/PA3"
      }
    },
    {
      "name": "Bash",
      "args": {
        "command": "STM32_PROGRAMMER_DEFAULT_SN=066DFF485754727567021514 stm32 debug read-peripheral GPIOA Projects/NUCLEO-L476RG/Examples/PWR/VCP-ECHO/STM32CubeIDE/Debug/VCP-ECHO.elf > /tmp/gpioa.json 2>&1; python3 -c \"\nimport json\nd=json.load(open('/tmp/gpioa.json'))\ndef walk(o,p=''):\n    if isinstance(o,dict):\n        for k,v in o.items(): walk(v,p+'/'+str(k))\n    elif isinstance(o,list):\n        for i,v in enumerate(o): walk(v,p+'/'+str(i))\n    else:\n        if any(s in p for s in ('MODER','AFRL','OTYPER','PUPDR')): print(p,'=',o)\n\"",
        "description": "Dump GPIOA JSON and extract MODER/AFRL/OTYPER/PUPDR entries"
      }
    },
    {
      "name": "Bash",
      "args": {
        "command": "head -c 2500 /tmp/gpioa.json",
        "description": "Inspect raw read-peripheral JSON shape"
      }
    },
    {
      "name": "Bash",
      "args": {
        "command": "python3 -c \"\nimport json\nd=json.load(open('/tmp/gpioa.json'))\nfor rn,r in d['registers'].items():\n    if 'AFR' in rn:\n        print(rn, 'raw=0x%08x' % r['raw_value'])\n        for fn,f in sorted(r['fields'].items()):\n            print('  %-8s = %d' % (fn, f['raw_value']))\n\"",
        "description": "Extract AFRL/AFRH field values from GPIOA dump"
      }
    }
  ],
  "final_text": "Source code sets PA2/PA3 to `GPIO_AF7_USART2` \u2014 correct on paper. Now verifying the live register state on the L476RG (probe `066DFF\u2026`):\nThe SVD names it `GPIOA` directly:\n**Yes \u2014 the AF number is correct, both in source and on the live target.**\n\nUSART2 is assigned to **PA2 (TX) / PA3 (RX)** \u2014 the ST-LINK VCP pins on the NUCLEO-L476RG. On the STM32L476, USART2 on those pins requires **AF7**, and that's exactly what's there:\n\n**Source** (`VCP-ECHO/Src/main.c`, `HAL_UART_MspInit`):\n- `Pin = GPIO_PIN_2 | GPIO_PIN_3`, `Mode = GPIO_MODE_AF_PP`, `Alternate = GPIO_AF7_USART2` \u2713\n\n**Live hardware** (read via `stm32 debug read-peripheral GPIOA`, attached without reset on the L476RG probe `066DFF\u2026`):\n\n| Register/field | Value | Meaning |\n|---|---|---|\n| `MODER2` / `MODER3` | `2` / `2` | Alternate-function mode \u2713 |\n| `AFRL2` / `AFRL3` | `7` / `7` | **AF7 = USART2_TX / USART2_RX** \u2713 |\n| `AFRL` raw | `0x00007700` | Only pins 2\u20133 muxed; no stray AF on other low pins |\n| `OTYPER` | `0` on PA2/PA3 | Push-pull, as configured |\n\nSo the mux is wired exactly as intended \u2014 if you're chasing a UART problem, the AF routing isn't it. Next suspects would be the USART2 peripheral itself (BRR/CR1 \u2014 `stm32 debug read-peripheral USART2` will decode them) or the clock tree."
}